[
  "Thomas Bruch's retail fortune derives from Globus, with roots dating back to 1828.",
  "Globus operates hypermarkets, plus DIY and electrical appliance stores, in Germany, Luxembourg, Russia and Czech Republic.",
  "Bruch personally owns just over 48% of the company, with the rest held by family members, a family foundation and a charitable foundation.",
  "The charitable Globus Stiftung -- of which Bruch's wife, Graciela, is CEO -- holds just over 26% and will inherit Bruch's stake after his death.",
  "In 2020, Thomas and Graciela's son Matthias took over as managing director of Globus, representing the sixth generation of the family to run the firm."
]